).

In Greek mythology, Zephyrus or Zephyr (Greek: 
Ζέφυρος
), is the god of the West Wind. He was reported to have had several wives in different stories, one of which was the nymph Chloris, upon whom he bestowed the domain of the flowers. The Romans later raised her status to goddess and gave her the name of Flora - the Latin name for flowers.
